1)    Prevention (SOP GI, Contingency (SOP GI-015) and Emergency Response Plans (SOP GI-010); which provides guidelines for responding to various emergencies such as fires, hazardous material spills, personal injuries, severe weather events, and property damage that may occur at the Flexitank Depot and headquarters facilities;

2)    Employees participate (SOP AD019), at least once a year, on safety and release prevention program; it provides the essential planning and training for effectively protecting our employees, the company, the environment, and the property; before, during and after an emergency situation; 

3)    Training (SOP AD019), is provided for all operations personnel such as: drivers, operators, maintenance, equipment control, general operations and customer service personnel; 

4)    Our emergency response program (ERT) (SOP GI-010); includes Spill Containment and an  "in-house" emergency response HAZMAT team (SOP OD014) and is supported by local Incident and Emergency Response Contractors;

5)    Process Safety Information (SOP OD003) is maintained on ammonia, TDI and other hazardous materials;

6)    A Hazard Assessment (SOP GI014 & OD013) is conducted periodically to ensure adequacy of controls, and processes;

7)    The Preventive maintenance program (SOP OP009) ensures the mechanical integrity of the equipment and its pressure relief and vapor control systems continue to operate as designed; 

8)    Operating SOP's (OP002) provides all personnel with the information necessary to safely transport and store equipment;

9)    Contractors or visitors working on our Depot facility require a work permit (SOP OD 019) provided by the QHSSE team. As part of the SOP, all visit

ors are briefed on the hazards and safety requirements of the job; and are trained to respond in case of release (Safety Briefing SOP GI-005); 

10)    Hot Work Permits (SOP OD017) are required whenever welding, cutting, grinding or other activities are conducted that could generate sparks and start a fire; 

11)    Formal Incident investigations (SOP GI029) are conducted for incidents involving any and all releases and near misses that endanger employees or the public;

12)    Compliance Audits (SOP QMD003) are conducted periodically to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives; 

13)    Responsible Care Quality Management System (PL-040) is in place as Flexitank Quality Policy;

14)    Management of Change (MOC) under SOP AD032 is in place to ensure project success, avoid loss of employees or customer's due to changes and minimize the impact on productivity 

15)    Pre-TRIP Safety Review (PTSR) are created "custom made" for ammonia, TDI and other hazardous products or substances. (SOP OD003/0D009)

16)    Departmental / Safety Meetings -QMD002 each department under must perform periodical safety meetings and report finding to the Safety Committee. 

17)    Facility Safety Committee is composed of the top managers of the company and meet periodically to discuss reports. (QMD 002)
